'''"No shit, Sherlock"''' was a common expression in the [[1990s|90s]] referring to dialogue between the characters [[Doctor Watson]] and [[Sherlock Holmes|Sherlock]] in Sir [[Arthur Conan Doyle]]'s mystery series, [[Sherlock Holmes]].

The statement is usually jokingly directed at someone who makes an utterly obvious statement, by sarcastically attributing the name of a detective who makes brilliant deductions. The reality is that they showed not only minimal intelligence but also stupidity. A somewhat common retort is "Keep looking Watson".

